<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Lesson 02 Selectors</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>

  <article>
    <h1>Selectors Practice</h1>

    <h2>Links</h2>
    <p>Here is a link inside the article: 
      <a href="https://example.com">Example Link</a>
    </p>

    <h3>Me Neither!</h3>
    <p>This heading should be italic.</p>

    <h3 class="custom-heading">Not Me!</h3>
    <p>
      Im becoming more comfortable with CSS, especially now that I understand how selectors work. 
      Chapter 3 helped me see how type, class, and descendant selectors control the look of a webpage. 
      I also learned how important structure is, because the way elements are nested affects which styles apply.
    </p>

  </article>

</body>
</html>
/* Make all headings share styles using :is() */
:is(h1, h2, h3) {
  font-weight: bold;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

/* Descendant selector for hyperlink inside article */
article a {
  color: green;
}

/* Italic “Me Neither!” heading */
h3 {
  font-style: italic;
}

/* Custom class for “Not Me!” heading */
.custom-heading {
  color: purple;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  font-style: normal; /* overrides the italic from h3 */
}
